This paper deals with modeling the evolution of line of sight blockage for vehicle-to-vehicle (V2V) channels, which is a topic related to wireless communication networks. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves probability theory and Markov chains, which are topics related to information theory, so cs.IT (Information Theory) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also uses curve fitting and distance-dependent equations, which are topics related to mathematical analysis, so cs.MA (Mathematical Analysis) is another likely sub-category. The paper's focus on vehicular mobility and building and foliage locations suggests that it may also be relevant to control systems (cs.SY) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
